==English==

===Etymology===
Originally {{sco}} and Northern English dialects, probably of Scandinavian origin; ultimately imitative.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/skɜ:l/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɜː(r)l|-ɜː(r)l]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# To make a [[shrill]] sound, as of [[bagpipes]].
#:*'''1985''': Drums began to thump in a variety of rhythms.  The flautists were not sure what to play.  The shawm began to '''skirl'''. — Anthony Burgess, ''Kingdom of the Wicked''

